    <body>&lt;p&gt;The Deck is an Ubuntu-based penetration testing and forensics Linux distribution designed to run on the BeagleBoard-xM and BeagleBone. It has every tool you will likely need and more and is great for penetration testing on the go and for drop boxes. A complete system easily fits in a child&apos;s lunch box.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.amazon.com/Hacking-Penetration-Testing-Power-Devices-ebook/dp/B00NGLLN56/ref=as_sl_pc_ss_til?tag=bloghanerhead-20&amp;amp;linkCode=w01&amp;amp;linkId=UMVNTI6ZZDIOU6LP&amp;amp;creativeASIN=B00NGLLN56&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../../static/images/hacking_and_pen_testing.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;80%&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Phil also has an associated book called &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.amazon.com/Hacking-Penetration-Testing-Power-Devices-ebook/dp/B00NGLLN56/ref=as_sl_pc_ss_til?tag=bloghanerhead-20&amp;amp;linkCode=w01&amp;amp;linkId=UMVNTI6ZZDIOU6LP&amp;amp;creativeASIN=B00NGLLN56&quot;&gt;Hacking and Penetration Testing with Low Power Devices&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</body>
